HEADWORD: Romeite
<hw>Ro"me*ite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
}</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>rom⟦eacute⟧ine</ets>. So calledafter
the French mineralogist <ets>Rom⟦eacute⟧</ets> L'Isle.]</ety>
<fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A mineral of a hyacinth or honey-yellow color,
occuring in square octahedrons. It is an antimonate of
calcium.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

